FBIS3-28803 "dreas028_d_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-028 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Feb 1994 South Korea Kim Il-song Reportedly Asks for U.S. Relations SK0902231494 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 2203 GMT 9 Feb 94 SK0902231494 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network Language: Korean Article Type:BFN [By Chi Chong-hak from Paris] [Text] France's LE FIGARO reported yesterday that North Korea proposed the establishment of diplomatic relations with the United States as a condition for abandoning its nuclear weapons development. The paper reported that North Korean President Kim Il-song said this in his letter to U.S. President Clinton, and that President Kim Il-song also expressed his intention to continue developing nuclear weapons if the condition is not met.
